reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Prefect bag for the cup !
reviews.reviewText: Bag has adjustable strap and seems pretty sturdy . Very nice color and came with a cute top for straw . Love the compartments , big enough for chapstick phone & car keys . Well made ! 😀

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works well! Fits like a glove.
reviews.reviewText: It does have a weird smell but it fades after a few days. It fits the 40oz Stanley like a glove and makes transporting so much easier. Fits my iPhone 14 great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Got a pink one and a cream colored one! They fit my 40 oz. Quenchers very nicely! Love that they protect them ! I put different straps on them , actually colorful guitar straps! Good price and good quality!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Using a Reduce 40oz - tight fit on top but still functions as needed.
reviews.reviewText: I liked that this product came with a straw cover, pockets, and Velcro closure. I got the 40oz option for my Reduce cup. The pink color looks great too! It fits snug on the cup and goes a tad bit high in the lips of the cup itself, which does not bother me. I mainly use the straw to drink from it. I know it was made for cups like Stanley’s. The bag sometimes needs to be pulled up more often, again, my handle is not like a Stanley’s so it may ride down. And the it’s made it less car cup holder friendly due to the increase in size.Pockets so far - I have a slim snack bar in the big one and a tube of lotion and chapstick in the smaller one. It’s made it kind of bulky and awkward. And I haven’t added keys to the carabiner yet because of this.Strap - I’m larger on top and the size of the band works for me comfortably when using as a cross body. The strap will fit around the waist but with how bulky the pockets and the cup are, I’m not confident it would work well to walk around with on the hip.My only complaint with this is the smell of the inside of the bag was strong and smells like balsamic vinegar. Even after airing it out in the garage for a few days, it can still be smelled, with less potency.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Daughter loves! So practical!
reviews.reviewText: Bought this for my daughter, and she loves being able to carry her travel cup with this crossbody holder. Has a clip to attach keys, a pocket big enough for her phone, and a second pocket that holds credit cards/cash, etc. Bith pockets have zippers, for added security. It comes in a box, and it did have a slight neoprene smell, but that dissipated quickly. This is a great grab-and-go option when you don’t want to juggle a purse with your travel cup. Very happy with this purchase!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I was very keen on keeping it as it felt durable and accommodated my tumbler perfectly. Although I can't confirm if this applies to all cell phones, it would have been inconvenient for me to access my phone regularly throughout the day. Despite my willingness to overlook this, the overpowering smell forced me to return it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Lightweight, durable and easy to use. Looks like my Brumate will fit but, my cellphone definitely WON’T. No big deal, I usually carry it in my back pocket. I love the super cute cloud straw cap!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fits Simply Modern Cup and iPhone
reviews.reviewText: It fits my black simply modern cup great! I will be ordering a black one to match my cup. For my pink Stanley, it looks a little weird. The bottom isn’t tight enough and it is a little too tall for my cup but it will work so I will be keeping it. It came with a cute little cloud straw topper though and it fits my iPhone 13 Pro (i don’t think it would fit a plus).I bought these to use on an upcoming cruise - it’s nice to have the zipper pocket so I can keep my card and phone inside it.

reviews.reviewTitle: This is ridiculously big, but awesome
reviews.reviewText: I put 6 big ice cubes in this thing at 5:30 am drank my icy drink over the next 5 hours, topped up the drink and the ice just kept going - the ice only melted and my drink was still cold about another 5 hours later. Everyone laughs at my stupidly big mug, but they all want one too!
